  "text": "C. difficile can be classified into 5 major clades (Clade 1-5) and 2 novel clades (Clade 6, C-I) using MLST [CITATION_1] . [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In the current study, the three isolates were assigned to ST-3, ST-15 and ST129, which have been identified in patients with diarrhoea in Eastern China [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . These results indicate the potential for C. difficile to be transmitted from pets to humans.",
